reviews.text: Absolutely a fun time!!! Definitely check out this attraction! The employees are so helpful, polite and entertaining!! I chose the package deal and it was definitely worth the money and time I absolutely enjoyed myself!!! Thanks again Curtis you definitely made the evening entertaining. Go visit this attraction and enjoy!

This is the first "wax museum" I've gone to, as I've always thought of them as kind of tacky.  BUT, I was pleasantly surprised!  This was done very well, with some really good figures.  The rules are "don't touch the hands or the face", but they have multiple places you can dress or hold props, or be part of the "scene" being depicted for photos, so that makes it more fun.  They've got a good mix of new and old, male and female...and alien...and horror characters and monsters, etc. Speaking of, the one thing I'd recommend is a way to bypass entirely the "horror movie" figures.  I'm sure I'm not alone in this - I have a daughter that's old enough that she knows many of the figures, but still young enough that they really scare her.  After some prodding and pushing, I got her to hold my hand, stare at the stairs and floor and run through the "dungeon scene".   That being said, I don't know if that would even be possible, but the only other option would be to go back out the way we came, and then see if they'd let us go backward into the end of the museum.  There may not be any way to arrange it differently. Overall, it was a fun experience, and the "combo ticket" which includes the "Castle of Chaos" (interactive 4d movie/ride thing), the mini-golf, and the mirror maze, was well worth the cost of admission.

Been here a lot. Best place ever! I love this place. Best place in Branson. I really hope this stays forever. It’s cool, fun and takes up at least an hour-2. Plus guess what they have this amazing 4-D experience there is no way to describe it you just have to go!!!

We had so much fun here! The price included the wax museum, an interactive game, put put and a mirror maze. I would def recommend for families and couples alike! You can do the wax museum by itself but it only costs a few bucks extra to do all the other stuff I mentioned... definitely worth it. Oh and it’s interactive with the wax figures so you can take pictures and dress up with props! Super fun.

Family and I loved this place. The wax models were so realistic. They have props to make photographs more enjoyable. We took lots of pictures. Nothing was rushed and the staff were so friendly. I recommend this to everyone.

They have great food and I love going there but they need more parking and def. need more seating at the location in Branson. I love the food and the service is really great they always check up on you. Their food is home-made and really good. Think that they need someone to manage their social media/reviews better and they need to update their area for Danna’s restaurant. Other than that I love it here💛

I loved my Carolina Piggy sandwich so much for lunch that I decided I would be back later in the day for dinner. There are so many options to choose from that look and smell great. The desserts look amazing. I'll be trying the bananas foster. Highly recommend. Everyone in my party enjoyed their food.

This place was packed and the line was long, but by the time we ordered our food they had a table ready for us. The food came out in record time, we couldn't believe how quickly it went. We had the nachos, ribs, cheeseburger, and pork, it was delicious! The desserts looked pretty good but we were stuffed and couldn't try them out. We will definitely go back again!

I’ve tried catfish from the scorched plains and plateaus of Arizona, the colossal peaks of the Rockies, to the forest and hills of Tennessee, the beaches of Florida and Alabama, and the meadows of Nebraska and Oklahoma, but never in my life have I had catfish so good! Now the coleslaw was great (obviously not better than old grandmas!) but was sweet and tasty! The roll was soft and buttered yet crisped to perfection as well, the fries were awesome also as was the beans that came with it. I highly recommend this place, staff is friendly, building is comfortable and rustic, and the food is literally immaculate!
We came during lunch time and it was very busy but our food still came out very quickly and was hot and fresh. Delicious! Would definitely come back. Also the staff was very friendly and helpful.

So this was the buffet that was part of the Grand Country Resort.  I'll review the resort later.  The buffet was very nice. My daughter and I partook of the dinner buffet once, and the breakfast buffet multiple times.  The place was clean and neat, well taken care of.  The buffet is not "Golden Corral" (or similar) large, but it did have a full salad bar with a few soups, a fruit/etc. bar,  and the main buffet with a small assortment of desserts (and yes, I had to look up if it was one or two "s's" in that). The dinner bar  had a small carving station, the breakfast bar had an omelet station. The staff was very friendly, and very busy...making sure your drink was topped off and you had more plates than you needed. The price is pretty good too, especially for a "tourist trap" town. Breakfast for ~$10 a person, dinner for ~$15 a person, lunch in between that.   My only "complaint" would be that the HOURS for each period of the buffet are virtually non-posted. The opening and closing is available, but the switch over times are "nowhere to be found".  But who cares - the food was fresh, hot, tasty, and plentiful!

Our server was very attentive and I was pleased with the food.  My husband didn't think there was a huge selection, and it definitely did lean towards most of the food being fried.  The value was pretty good for what we got, though, and I think we'd go back!

Buffets are often a median range of 'ok' foods, but this one is an exception! Everything was so good! If I had to find one negative thing, it is simply we like our bacon a bit less crispy. However, there are PLENTY of other wonderful things! The supreme flaky croissants and luscious bread pudding with vanilla cream so lovely that I was tempted to make my meal out of them alone!
Nice variety.  Fresh food rotated onto the service line very frequently. Got a good deal using the Branson Guest Card.  Excellent table service!  Would definitely recommend.

Got there at 10:20am And was told the custom omelets ended at 10:30 and breakfast items would be removed at 11:00.
Omelets were good and the choices for toppings good. If we're were still hungry we could have eaten lunch items when they came out. It was like eating breakfast on a Carnival cruise ship.

We loved this place. Lively. Great food. I ordered the Devil's House salad twice on this trip. Blueberry Poppyseed dressing is YUMMY! Good burgers, too. Live music after 8:30 p.m. Be sure to take a little walk to see the bridge and Devil's Pool right outside the door.

For non-country fans, the band was fabulous! Very funny and awesome musicians! Jenny, who played the violin, was amazing! Thanks for the special Norwegian anniversary songs! We totally loved it! The chicken livers and chicken wings were great too! What a fabulous way to spend our anniversary! Thanks Clay Self, band and the Buzzard Bar! See you next visit! The Norwegian & his Girlfriend

3 star food, 5 star prices...

Our family of 5 ate for $90; no desert or appetizer included.  For the food we received, we would normally pay $50-$60.  Portions are small.  

On the bright side, service was fantastic!  I guess they are happy to rip customers off!

All apart of the location I guess.

This a great restaurant.  It is very cozy, with a nice view.  The menu is varied and you can order from the devil's pool menu as well.  The cat fish was awesome and the fries are perfect.  The smoked trout appetizer is excellent, moist with great flavor.  Their selection of meat and salmon are well prepared and very tasty.  We eat there every time we visit big cedar.
Love the singing cowboy.  The food is good

Great atmosphere and staff at the rustic camping-themed casual restaurant.  I found the dinner options just as high quality as Osage at 1/2 the price. Entrees are not of the same character, but match in quality. I especially like the salads here, but additional protein is too high in cost. Pulled pork sandwich and sweet potato chips paired well. I prefer my pork more wet, so requested additional sauce.  Dessert menu has nice options for close. 

Kids pizza works well.  We also tried the kids pasta and it was a hit.
We visited Devil's Pool restaurant twice for breakfast while visiting Big Cedar Lodge. Very good omelettes!! And the servers were super helpful and friendly!! Definitely worth a stop!!

Super good Kansas City Strip Steak! Donel, our server, was so attentive and welcoming. She had the gift of hospitality. We met Jarod, a new manager, who stayed to talk with us. The atmosphere was very charming, rustic lodge with fireplaces. Service time was good. We will definitely go back to Devil's Pool.
Wonderful atmosphere! The waitress was the best I have ever had. Food was incredible and the prices quite reasonable. Will definitely be coming back

The roasted duck appeared and tasted as if it was microwaved. I had to send it back due to it being raw when I recieved it. My wife’s salmon was good, but not worth the price we paid. The old fashion was acceptable, but could have been better, too top heavy due to being allowed to sit to long before being served. The house beer was excellent though.

The restaurant has some charm with interesting signs and gift shop. The food is ok however the service is fairly slow even when the restaurant is mostly empty. The staff is friendly. Catching rolls is a fun activity to keep you busy while waiting for food but the rolls are below average taste.

Fast and very nice service. Catfish was to die for! I had a baked sweet potato with pecan cinnamon butter. First time I’ve had this kind of butter and it was delicious! We should be back in Branson this summer, planning to come back.
Fun place to eat! We all caught the buns they threw at us!! Good food! Window seat, lots to look at inside also.
Food is just okay. But a lot of fun for the kids. The throwing rolls are fun. Service is good. Clean and nice.

Our server was nice and attentive. But greens on salad bar looked a little old. Steaks were overcooked , sent back and was corrected. The steak had an odd flavor. Management dig give small discount due to our dissatisfaction.

We absolutely LOVE the Rowdy Beaver! The wait staff is always nice and the food is always great! We go there at least 3 times a year and we have enjoyed it every time we have been
We recommend this place to everyone that visits the Eureka Springs area!

The band that was playing live music was wonderful,  I knew all the songs. Had a great time. The band sounded great.
Our waitress came to our table one time and did not return. 
We had to flag down another waitress to get some service.

Excellent food! The service was great and the food came out quickly! The gift store inside was great too...tshirts were hilarious! 

My advice: get the buffalo wings and be sure to try the fries 😉

We were in the Rowdy Beaver April 5th, 2019 with a big group of the CVMA chapter 7-2 Motorcycle Riders! I was the only woman in the group! Anyway, we had a great time! The food was good the service was great! Our waitress was a trooper! And she did a great job! Thank you for helping to start out a great weekend in Eureka Springs, AR!

We went to this little restaurant while we was on our honeymoon in Eureka Springs. Guaranteed to get seated quickly. The food was good. The Prime rib was very good. Service was good as well. We was there during Mardi Gra,  so they had their float out front for viewing.

They have great food and I love going there but they need more parking and def. need more seating at the location in Branson. I love the food and the service is really great they always check up on you. Their food is home-made and really good. Think that they need someone to manage their social media/reviews better and they need to update their area for Danna’s restaurant. Other than that I love it here💛

I loved my Carolina Piggy sandwich so much for lunch that I decided I would be back later in the day for dinner. There are so many options to choose from that look and smell great. The desserts look amazing. I'll be trying the bananas foster. Highly recommend. Everyone in my party enjoyed their food.

This place was packed and the line was long, but by the time we ordered our food they had a table ready for us. The food came out in record time, we couldn't believe how quickly it went. We had the nachos, ribs, cheeseburger, and pork, it was delicious! The desserts looked pretty good but we were stuffed and couldn't try them out. We will definitely go back again!

We came during lunch time and it was very busy but our food still came out very quickly and was hot and fresh. Delicious! Would definitely come back. Also the staff was very friendly and helpful.
The manager told us to come on in and then she said she didnt have any rooms available once we got there. We know for a fact from several people that they have rooms.
New owners have fixed it up nice. Pool is gorgeous. Nice laundry facilities as well.

Mostly caters to weekly rentals. Nice rooms with flat screen TVs that include cable and a few movies channels. They also have a dorm size refrigerator and a microwave. Security is very tight with multiple cameras. And also has a very nice swimming pool with Grill area. The laundry room is a little on the high side as far as cost goes. The management could be a little more polite but some people are just jerks but as far as Candlelight and goes it's an okay place
Location was cute and the rooms are well kept. The service is friendly and its close to town
Very clean very safe. Nice rooms. Sweet owners

To my girl Brittney (awesome service and beyond welcoming) best chicken teriyaki yet (hot, fresh, and delicious).I was supposed to post a photo of this fine sandwich but the hunger took over and destroyed half the sandwich (sorry Brittney). If you hit the landing swing by the store and let Brittney craft you the most amazing lunch you will have that week. Unless you live with Chef Gordan Ramsey and he's available for lunch. Thanks crew keep up the good work.

We were very impressed with the Charleys Philly subs in Branson on the Landing. The people who worked there were on top of things and got the huge line through in a timely manner. The food was excellent. Job well done Branson Charleys!!!!!

The sandwiches are very good and cooked right in front of you.  The ultimate fries have real bacon on them and are very good.   The best thing they have is the fresh strawberry lemonade.  The staff act like they hate their jobs.  They do everything like it seems they were programmed to do but without any emotion and pleasantries.
Sandwiches were great! The flavored lemonades were phenomenal!
Good food, but read the fine print before purchasing. Some food sold separately.

This was our first time and wow, super impressed! Kaylee was our waitress and she is one of those rare individuals who exude happiness. Prices were high but when you figure on the double portion size, not bad at all. A must do for those visiting Branson and a will do over and over for locals.  Ask to be seated in Kaylee's section, she is the best!

I love this place! They offer fun bibs with fun comments on them for people ordering the big buckets. They gave my date one, too, saying they didn't want her to feel left out. The crab legs that I ordered were delicious and the cooked veggies tasted amazing. I had so much food that I had plenty to eat as a midnight snack later.

I am a huge fan of crab so I like to go to Joe's Crab Shack whenever I am in the area! I always get the steam pots and I am never disappointed! You get a nice variety of crab legs, potatoes, shrimp, sausage and corn. They also have the restuarant placed right by the lake so the views are fantastic. I will definitely be back again!

The food was great. Our waitress, Breeana, was hopping busy but still had time to stop and grab any items we requested. Something huge for me, they have a gluten free menu! There were no issues with the menu request either. (Not everyone is kind when you have to request something gluten free.) My daughter absolutely loved "painting" her dessert. My other daughter even got full and had to take food home. (Something rare for a growing girl like her!) We hope to go back on our next trip to Branson.

For the price the food wasn't great, it was more along the lines of captain d's or long john silvers. The drinks were mostly just a mix without any alcohol, should have been top shelf for the size and price. Disappointed that we spent $100 for a dinner for two and could have had a similar experience at a fast food place. We even were seated at a table in a corner with baby seats blocking the view which would have been the only good thing about the place. I feel like we wasted our money and the trip to Branson for dinner.

Took my for kids there. I have 4 under 4 LOL and it was great, the service was speedy and courteous they put on a show for the kids.  The hibachi was great. I also went their separate time with my wife just for us and the service and the food were awesome

Great fun and yummy food. My friend and I found this place while on vacation in Branson. We weren't up to going to any of the dinner show places around. There are plenty of those in town.
A Japanese steakhouse is a specialty restaurant. Between 8 to 10 ppl are seated around a large grilling station. The chef cooks the food in front of you, adding a great deal of showmanship and entertainment. It's a fun evening and the food is fantastic.
We were seated at a table immediately and the rest of the table filled in within a few minutes. We ordered the scallops and the chicken and both were very good.
I really like this place and recommend it highly.

Great sushi, great saki bombs too...
We had the sweetest waitress ever!!! Atmosphere was cozy and quiet loved it..
Great hibachi, we went there for our anniversary and we were seated right away! Would definitely go again.
The food was really good but you can tell when they bring in the off season help

The food was really good but you can tell when they bring in the off season help

Would have been a 5-star review if the bartender hadn’t been such a you-know-what...

The atmosphere, live music, drinks, and fried pickles were great, but sitting at the bar was probably not our best move. The bartender acted as though my husband and I were an inconvenience, and I know it wasn’t personal. She was like that to everyone. If there were more than 4 people at the bar, she would get visibly irritated. The second that there were less people, she’d get a little less you-know-what-y... Then irritated when more people walked up, and so on and so on. 

I’m not one to tip nothing at all, but we left her something small enough that we’re hoping she got the hint. Overall, just a poor experience. We’re not from around here, but we wouldn’t come back even if we were.

It was a pretty good attempt at an Irish pub.  The menu has a decent selection of food and drinks.  The food I ordered wasn't bad.  The waitress was almost non existent but I'm sure she was just busy.  It looked like there was only 2 of them.  The below average band's attempt at music and obnoxious customers cackling along is what made me not want to be there.  I'd give it another shot on another night.

Would love to talk about my experience with the food. Unfortunately, did not get to have any, I walked out after 30 minutes of waiting for someone to ask if we wanted any drinks. They weren't busy either.
The Scotch Eggs are well worth it. Great Irish/Scottish food. Now I was there when there was live music hard to talk or hear when the music drowns out everything else

We really enjoyed the food! The fish and chips portions were huge! The offer great specials throughout the week and are conveniently located at Branson Landing. The service wasn’t as good as I would have expected, they weren’t busy enough to have such mediocre performance.
